# QA Requirements Reference Points

Every piece of test work is evaluated against this list during Phase 1 (requirements curation). For each item, the curated requirements record one of:

- **Addressed** — the change covers this; the test will verify it
- **Flagged gap** — concern applies but input doesn't address it; engineer dispositions during review
- **Not applicable** — with a brief reason

Gaps caught at Phase 1 are cheap. The same concern surfacing during Phase 4 is expensive.

## Item statuses

- **Active** — applied to every Phase 1 evaluation; gaps are blocking
- **Proposed** — documented, not yet enforced; gaps are informational
- **Deprecated** — kept for history, not applied

---

## Universal / Cross-cutting

### Security

| Reference point | Status |
|---|---|
| Authentication boundaries — verify authenticated and unauthenticated paths | Proposed |
| Authorisation checks — verify denied/allowed paths for permission gates | Proposed |
| Input validation — malformed / over-long / encoded payloads | Proposed |
| Sensitive data handling — PII, credentials, tokens must not appear in responses, logs, or URLs | Proposed |

### Error handling

| Reference point | Status |
|---|---|
| Graceful failure modes — system fails predictably when upstream services misbehave | Proposed |
| User-facing error messages — clear, actionable, no internal details leaked | Proposed |
| No leaked diagnostics — stack traces, debug info, version strings must not surface to users | Proposed |

### Performance

| Reference point | Status |
|---|---|
| Latency budget per scenario — defined at authoring time, asserted in test where applicable | Proposed |
| Behaviour under typical load — applies if change is in a hot path | Proposed |

### Observability

| Reference point | Status |
|---|---|
| Logging coverage — new events logged at appropriate levels; no PII in logs | Proposed |
| Trace propagation — trace context preserved across service boundaries | Proposed |
| Metrics emission — new metrics fire correctly; named consistently | Proposed |

### Internationalisation

| Reference point | Status |
|---|---|
| Locale support — works across officially supported locales | Proposed |
| Character set handling — UTF-8 / non-Latin / RTL inputs | Proposed |
| Date / time / timezone — renders and stores in right zone; no UTC drift | Proposed |

### Backward compatibility

| Reference point | Status |
|---|---|
| Existing-behaviour preservation — change does not break what other tests depend on | Proposed |
| External contract stability — API contracts versioned/deprecated cleanly | Proposed |
| Deprecation notices — phased-out items have documented sunset path | Proposed |

