## UI-Specific

### Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

| Reference point | Status |
|---|---|
| Keyboard operability — every interactive element reachable/operable via keyboard | Proposed |
| Screen reader compatibility — aria attributes correct; reading order coherent | Proposed |
| Colour contrast — 4.5:1 text, 3:1 UI components | Proposed |
| Focus indication — visible, meaningful, not removed by custom styling | Proposed |
| Form labels and error association — inputs labelled; errors programmatically linked to fields | Proposed |
| Zoom resilience — layout intact at 200%/400% zoom | Proposed |

### Usability

| Reference point | Status |
|---|---|
| Loading states — long-running operations show meaningful feedback | Proposed |
| Empty states — first-use, no-data, no-results handled distinctly | Proposed |
| Error states — visible recovery path when things break | Proposed |
| Destructive-action confirmation — irreversible actions have a confirmation step | Proposed |

### Browser compatibility

| Reference point | Status |
|---|---|
| Cross-browser — Chromium / Firefox / WebKit (MS Edge channel for this project) | Proposed |

