## API-Specific

### Contract correctness

| Reference point | Status |
|---|---|
| Response schema — matches published contract | Proposed |
| Status codes — match contract; no 200s with error bodies | Proposed |
| Error response shape — consistent envelope across endpoints | Proposed |

### Behaviour

| Reference point | Status |
|---|---|
| Rate limiting — enforced where contract says it is; correct headers returned | Proposed |
| Idempotency — methods that claim it actually exhibit it under retry | Proposed |
| Pagination — contract behaviour preserved; consistent across endpoints | Proposed |
| Versioning — backward compatibility within a published version | Proposed |

